ypically infernally bad taste.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Engrish" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Engrish">Engrish</a>: Gunvarell, most likely (or intentionally) a corruption of "gunbarrel", the name for the in-series mecha anim&eacute; and robot.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FantasyForbiddingFather" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FantasyForbiddingFather">Fantasy-Forbidding Father</a>: Subaru's dad is very much against him trying to pursue a career in robotics and instead wants him to be a fisherman like himself. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">And after Gunbuild 2 accidentally falls on top of him, it gives his father more credibility as to why he shouldn't be working with robots.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FoolishSiblingResponsibleSibling" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FoolishSiblingResponsibleSibling">Foolish Sibling, Responsible Sibling</a>: Akiho and her older sister, Misaki.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foreshadowing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foreshadowing">Foreshadowing</a>/<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrickJoke" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrickJoke">Brick Joke</a>:<ul><li> Episode 4<div class="indent"><strong>Akiho</strong>: "So If I also defeat you (at <em>Kill Ballad</em>), I'll be your superior?"</div><div class="indent"><strong>Kaito</strong>: "I guess, but I doubt you could ever win, even in a hundred games..."</div></li><li> Episode 6<div class="indent"><strong>Kaito</strong> (to Junna): "The wind's strong around here. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeadpanSnarker" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeadpanSnarker">I would suggest sleeping on the runway,</a> but this time of the season that could be <em>fatal,</em> so be careful."</div></li><li> Episode 7<div class="indent"><strong>Misaki (young)</strong>: ''You need to